  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dbd\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0db4\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The coalition parties kick Namal's proposal",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that the group of nine joint parties has rejected a proposal made by Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna Member of Parliament Mr. Namal Rajapaksa that the government should be changed and a new government should be formed together.",
        "MP Namal Rajapakse informed this proposal in a separate meeting with MP Vasudeva Nanayakkara yesterday, and Mr. Vasudeva Nanayakkara is reported to have announced Namala's proposal to the party leaders during the discussion of the leaders of the nine joint parties held at the Communist Party headquarters last Tuesday.",
        "Political sources say that the proposal was strongly rejected by all the party leaders.",
        "The leaders of the joint parties have commented on this matter and stated that since the Rajapaksas are responsible for this crisis, they are no longer able to govern with them.",
        "Therefore, political sources state that the leaders of the joint parties have decided not to hold any discussion with the MP Namal Rajapaksa in this regard."
      ],
